	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000994_0001"/><!--pb/@n='18r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">10<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> April </p>
<lb/><p>My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose a 
<lb/>cheque for Â£30 
<lb/>to be sent to my 
<lb/>brother <persName>Rev<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi> Charles 
<lb/>Livingstone</persName> of <placeName>Mattapoisett</placeName>
<lb/><placeName>Massachusetts</placeName>
<lb/><placeName>United States</placeName><reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000994_0002"/><!--pb/@n='18v'--> 
<lb/>It is the first use 
<lb/>I have put any 
<lb/>of the Fund about 
<lb/>which we talked 
<lb/>in the way. He 
<lb/>has lost his health 
<lb/>and wishes in 
<lb/>consequence to 
<lb/>go out with 
<lb/>me to <placeName>Africa</placeName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>his is to pay 
<lb/>his passage. His 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000994_0003"/><!--pb/@n='19r'--> 
<lb/>church gives him 
<lb/>only 800 dollars 
<lb/>per annum and 
<lb/>another church 
<lb/>near <placeName>Boston</placeName>
<lb/>is actually indebted 
<lb/>to him still a portion 
<lb/>of his salary of 
<lb/>former years<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>If you let me 
<lb/>know to whom 
<lb/>he is to apply in 
<lb/><placeName>Boston</placeName>, I shall 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_000994_0004"/><!--pb/@n='19v'--> 
<lb/>write and let him 
<lb/>know<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose the 
<lb/>note of <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Sharp</persName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Please return 
<lb/>the copy of the 
<lb/>I) first slip. I wish 
<lb/>to put in all the 
<lb/>corrections clearly 
<lb/>one leaf is rather 
<lb/>crowded in what 
<lb/>I have. I will then 
<lb/>let you have it<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p><persName>D. Livingstone</persName></p><addSpan spanTo="#p18r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p>It is 30 miles from <placeName>Boston</placeName></p><anchor xml:id="p18r-01"/>
			
</div>
